notes: Good examples of nominatives in this sentence. Nominatives on both subject and predicate
-iyi as stative/resultative, also not true reflexive. Add to examples under reflexives
locative on 1st person pronoun - not on the nominative stem? Also null imperative

4.translation-en: Yes I will go to you.
notes: locative on second person; good future example too. Locative as goal of motion (not allative)

6.translation-en: Yes I will go away from you.
notes: good example of the "factual" suffix, translated as a future but maybe more definite? note that -ba is on a verb here, can it go on other word classes?

7.full_text: niladha nhaniguru buka dhithiani ngawulanga ngandrangala yanhthadhikagali
7.translation-en: Yesterday those dogs came up to us at night.
notes: -guru on a nominative. what other cases can it go on? does it only go on pronouns or can it go on other items too?

8.translation-en: All those dogs are coming up together.

9.translation-en: (I) feel cold. Light the fire quick.
